        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 5:06PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 505 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elsie, or 7 miles east of St. Johns, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Owosso, New Lothrop, Corunna, Henderson, Juddville, and Carland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
